The paper deals with hyperspectral image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is based on Graph Convolutional Network (GCN), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves learning the adjacency matrix and edge filter, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves refining the graph structure, which is a graph theory concept (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves training the model using backpropagation, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
